    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\n- `vim.system` does not support `pty` option, unlike `jobstart`.\r\n- Neither `jobstart` nor `pty` support a `term` option. Supporting `term` would eliminate the need for `termopen`.\r\n\r\n# Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`vim.system(..., { pty = true })` works like `jobstart(..., { pyt = true })`.\r\n\r\n## Technical notes\r\n\r\n- jobstart's \"pty\" option is handled as a special case (not delegated to libuv): https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/cc87dda31a5b5637ade7ddcfe5199f2df5fd47df/src/nvim/os/pty_process_unix.c#L163\r\n\r\nvia @bfredl : \r\n\r\n> last time I checked `uv_spawn` lacked some wiring to be used together with `openpty()` (instead of using `forkpty()` ), maybe we could convince libuv to add that..\r\n> ie you can already open a pty master/slave pair and send the slave fd's to `uv_spawn`, but it doesn't become the controlling terminal then.\r\n> `TIOCSCTTY` needs to be done in the child before `execve()` the new process.\r\n",
